Consumption over the past week was 685 million litres a day, which is 15 million litres under the collective usage target of 700 million litres a day. The City announced the latest dam levels amid the worst drought in three decades. Currently there are an estimated 99 days' water left. 
Dam levels have declined to 24.1% (storage levels), which is 1% down from a week ago. With the last 10% of a dam’s water not being useable, dam levels are effectively at 14.1%. With a usage target of 700 million litres a day,  mayoral committee  member for informal settlements, water and waste services; and energy, Xanthea Limberg praised residents who saved water, but urged them to continue to do so, at least for the next year. The announcement comes amid increasing efforts to save water, including pressure reduction in certain areas.“To give our residents an idea of the seriousness of the situation, we'll be lowering the consumption target to 600 million litres soon,” said Limberg.